<div id="community-vibe">
    <h2 class="sect-title">Community Vibe in Hillhurst</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Residing within Hillhurst is Kensington Business Revitalization Zone (BRZ). </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Whilst sharing the zone with Sunnyside, Kensington lies mostly in Hillhurst and has become a popular, trendy area, full of shops, restaurants and coffee/tea shops. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Famous places include Broken Plate Greek restaurant, Kensington Pub, and Oolong Tea House. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Kensington hosts Salsa Festival in July and Christmas in Kensington Village in December. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Shopping in Kensington is varied, with art stores (fitting for its proximity to ACAD), unique clothing boutiques, and other accessories. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Along with Memorial Drive is the Bow River walkway, extending down a majority of the Bow River as in encompasses the downtown core. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The pathway leads to several Calgary attractions, including Eau Claire Market/Princes Island and The Calgary Zoo. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The walkway is a great place for recreation and for quick walks to popular Calgary destinations.</p>

            <p class="par-lg">Hillhurst has three public schools run by the CBE, a community school, and elementary and a junior high/high school. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The Catholic School Board also has a fine arts elementary school. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">SAIT Polytechnic has a home bordering the north of Hillhurst, overlooking the beautiful Calgary skyline.</p>

            <p class="par-lg">Medical clinics are available around Kensington area, from dentistry to family doctors. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Foothills Hospital is located just up the hill for major emergencies in the event one should happen. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Hillhurst shares a close community with Sunnyside, as Kensington is divided between the two neighbourhoods. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The nearest C-train station is Sunnyside station on the Somerset/Dalhousie line, making quick transport to almost all of Calgaryâ€™s attractions.</p>
        </div>
